sentences: Beans has released two LPs and one EP on AntiPop Consortium's former label Warp Records since launching his solo career in 2003:
The third solo album Only was released on Thirsty Ear Recordings in 2005, followed by the fourth album Thorns on Adored And Exploited in 2007
The third solo album Only was released on Thirsty Ear Recordings in 2005, followed by the fourth album Thorns on Adored And Exploited in 2007
In 2011, Beans released the fifth solo album, End It All.
In 2013, Beans collaborated with Ghostly International recording artist, Mux Mool, under the name, Knifefight.

In 2017, after a five-year hiatus and the completion of numerous simultaneous projects on his new imprint, Tygr Rawwk Rcrds, Beans has returned to the public eye with not one, but three new albums, as well as his first novel.
The name, HAAST, derives from an extinct species of eagle that once lived on the South Island of New Zealand around 1400.

Beans has collaborated with Vernon Reid of Living Colour, Kool A.D., Ghislain Poirier, Arto Lindsay, Alec Empire, Funkstörung, Holy Fuck, Evil Nine, DJ Shadow among others.
Die Tonight, 174 pages of weird fiction, tells the story of Eric Ford, a teenage loner who gets possessed by a record, goes on a killing spree, and finds himself.
The second album, Love Me Tonight, features various producers such as Sam Fogarino from Interpol, Gobby, Laurel Halo, Container, Ben Chisholm (Chelsea Wolfe), Tobacco, and Pete Swanson.
Love Me Tonight delves into love and all of its manifestations, both rewarding and costly.
In the past has taken to the stage armed with only a microphone and a portable CD player for his backing track, further reflecting the minimalist nature of his style.
He has been recently performing and touring with That Kid Prolific.
